#: ../../reference_manual/preferences/shortcut_settings.rst:18
msgid ""
"Configuring shortcuts is another way to customize the application to fit "
"you.  Whether you are transitioning from another app, like Photoshop or "
"MyPaint, or you think your own shortcut keys make more sense for you then "
"Krita has got you covered.  You get to the shortcuts interface through :"
"menuselection:`Settings --> Configure Krita...` and by choosing the :"
"menuselection:`Keyboard Shortcuts` tab."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/preferences/shortcut_settings.rst:20
msgid ""
"Most of Krita's shortcuts are configured in the menu section :menuselection:"
"`Settings --> Configure Krita... --> Shortcuts`. The shortcuts configured "
"here are simple key combinations, for example the :kbd:`Ctrl + X` shortcut "
"to cut. Shortcuts can also be sequences of key combinations (e.g. :kbd:"
"`Shift + S` shortcut then the :kbd:`B` key). Krita also has a special "
"interface for configuring the mouse and stylus events sent to the canvas, "
"found under :ref:`canvas_input_settings`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/preferences/shortcut_settings.rst:22
msgid ""
"To use, just type the :guilabel:`Action` into the Search box you want to "
"assign/reassign the shortcut for.  Suppose we wanted to assign the shortcut :"
"kbd:`Ctrl + G` to the :guilabel:`Action` of Group Layers so that every time "
"we pressed the :kbd:`Ctrl + G` shortcut a new Layer Group would be created.  "
"Use the following steps to do this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/preferences/shortcut_settings.rst:24
msgid "Type \"Group Layer\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/preferences/shortcut_settings.rst:25
msgid "Click on Group Layer and a small inset box will open."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/preferences/shortcut_settings.rst:26
msgid "Click the Custom radio button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/preferences/shortcut_settings.rst:27
msgid "Click on the first button and type the :kbd:`Ctrl + G` shortcut."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/preferences/shortcut_settings.rst:28
msgid "Click OK."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/preferences/shortcut_settings.rst:30
msgid ""
"From this point on, whenever you press the :kbd:`Ctrl + G` shortcut you'll "
"get a new :guilabel:`Group Layer`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/preferences/shortcut_settings.rst:33
msgid ""
"Smart use of shortcuts can save you significant time and further streamline "
"your workflow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/preferences/shortcut_settings.rst:37
msgid ""
"Actions, which includes everything that can be assigned a shortcut, can now "
"be searched with :kbd:`Ctrl + Enter`, reducing the need to assign a shortcut "
"to every single action. This itself is called the :guilabel:`Search Actions` "
"shortcut, and can also be reassigned if desired."
msgstr ""

